The article is about Vice President Kamala Harris visiting the Belmont Water Treatment Plant in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania to address the issue of clean drinking water in America. Harris emphasizes the importance of clean water and the negative consequences of water shortages, flooding, and lead contamination. She shares the story of a young boy named Aiden who suffered from lead poisoning due to contaminated tap water. Harris highlights the administration's commitment to investing in water infrastructure and removing lead pipes. She praises President Joe Biden's leadership and concludes by introducing Jana Curtis, a mother who has advocated for safe and healthy environments for children.